urnType Namespace="Recipe_Management">RecipeDescription</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>960</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>iIndex</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeIndexByName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Returns the index of the recipe or -1 if a recipe with this name is not found ]]></Comment><ReturnType>INT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>stName</Name><Type>STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>648</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeName</Name><ReturnType>STRING(80)</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>648</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>iIndex</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeNames</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Returns the recipe names from the corresponding recipedefinition 
Possible last error values:
ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET, ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND, ERR_FAILED, ERR_OK
Example:
We have 50 recipes. We want to create a table which shows 10 recipe names at a time.
We define a Stringarray strArr: ARRAY[0..9] OF STRING;
Corresponding to the iStartIndex we can get the recipe names from a specific area.
iStartIndex := 0; The names 0..9 are returned.
iStartIndex := 20; The names 20..29 are returned.
In this example:
iSize := 10;
]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pStrings</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ The strings where the recipe values should be stored ]]></Comment><Type>STRING(80)</Type><ArrayInfo PointerTo="1"><LBound>0</LBound><Elements>1</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iSize</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Size of the string array. ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iStartIndex</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Start index. Can be used for a scrolling function (See example)]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeValues</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Returns the recipe values from the corresponding recipe
Possible last error values:
ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET, ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND, ERR_RECIPE_NOT_FOUND, ERR_FAILED, ERR_OK
Example:
We have 50 recipe values. We want to create a table which shows 10 recipe values at a time.
We define a Stringarray strArr: ARRAY[0..9] OF STRING;
Corresponding to the iStartIndex we can implement a scrolling and we can fill the string array 
with every recipe value of the recipe.
iStartIndex := 0; The values 0..9 are returned.
iStartIndex := 20; The values 20..29 are returned.
In this example:
iStringLength := 80; 
iSize := 10;
]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pStrings</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ The strings where the recipe values should be stored ]]></Comment><Type>STRING(80)</Type><ArrayInfo PointerTo="1"><LBound>0</LBound><Elements>1</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iSize</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Size of the string array. ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iStartIndex</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Start index. Can be used for a scroll function (See example)]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iStringLength</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ String length of the strings in the array ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeVariableNames</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Returns the recipe variable names from the corresponding recipe. 
Possible last error values:
ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET, ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND, ERR_RECIPE_NOT_FOUND, ERR_FAILED, ERR_OK
Example:
We have 50 recipe values. We want to create a table which shows 10 recipe variable names at a time.
We define a Stringarray strArr: ARRAY[0..9] OF STRING;
Corresponding to the iStartIndex we can get the recipe variable names from a specific area.
iStartIndex := 0; The names 0..9 are returned.
iStartIndex := 20; The names 20..29 are returned.
In this example: 
iSize := 10;
]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pStrings</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ The strings where the recipe values should be stored ]]></Comment><Type>STRING(80)</Type><ArrayInfo PointerTo="1"><LBound>0</LBound><Elements>1</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iSize</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Size of the string array. ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iStartIndex</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Start index. Can be used for a scrolling function (See example)]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>LoadAll</Name><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>bClear</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>RegisterEventHandler</Name><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>handler</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinitionEventHandler</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>Reload</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Reloads the list of recipes from the file system 
]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>SaveAll</Name><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>SelectRecipe</Name><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>iIndex</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>SetRecipeValues</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Sets the recipe values into the corresponding recipe. 
Possible last error values:
ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET, ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND, ERR_RECIPE_NOT_FOUND, ERR_FAILED, ERR_OK
Example:
We have 50 recipe values. We want to create a table which shows 10 recipe values at a time.
We define a Stringarray strArr: ARRAY[0..9] OF STRING;
Corresponding to the iStartIndex we can set the recipe values from a specific area.
iStartIndex := 0; The values 0..9 are set.
iStartIndex := 20; The values 20..29 are set.
In this example:
iSize := 10;
]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pStrings</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ The strings with the recipe values ]]></Comment><Type>STRING(80)</Type><ArrayInfo PointerTo="1"><LBound>0</LBound><Elements>1</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iSize</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Size of the string array. ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iStartIndex</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Start index. Can be used for a scrolling function (See example)]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>UnregisterEventHandler</Name><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>handler</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinitionEventHandler</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management">InfoValues</Name><BitSize>32</BitSize><BaseType>UDINT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>NO_INFO</Text><Enum>0</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>INFO_RECIPE_MANAGER_NOT_ALL_VARIABLES_FOUND</Text><Enum>1</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ | During load recipe, with the load type "Load matching variables by variable name", some variables 
   from the application variable list were NOT in the recipe file. 
 | Possible reason: The application recipe definition was extended by new variables and the recipe file is older.]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>INFO_RECIPE_MANAGER_OTHER_VARIABLES_FOUND</Text><Enum>2</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ | During load recipe, with the load type "Load matching variables by variable name", some variables 
   from the recipe file were not in the application variable list.
 | Possible reason: Some variables where deleted in the application variable list and the recipe file is older.]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>INFO_RECIPE_MANAGER_ONE_OR_MORE_VARIABLES_FOUND</Text><Enum>4</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ | During load recipe, with the load type "Load matching variables by variable name", one ore more
   values were written into the application recipe. 
 | Possible reason: One or more variables were found in the recipe file which match to the application variable list.]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>INFO_RECIPE_MANAGER_ALL_VARIABLES_FOUND</Text><Enum>8</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ | During load recipe, with the load type "Load matching variables by variable name", all
   values were written into the application recipe.
 | Possible reason: All variables were found in the recipe file which match to the application variable list.]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeManager</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="Recipe_Management">IGeneric</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getCurrent</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getDefinitionCount</Name><ReturnType>INT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getLastError</Name><ReturnType>UDINT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getLastInfo</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management">InfoValues</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__setLastError</Name><Parameter><Name>LastError</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__setLastInfo</Name><Parameter><Name>LastInfo</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">InfoValues</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeDefinition</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>iIndex</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeDefinitionByName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Searches for a recipe definition with the given name and return the found one]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>stDefinitionName</Name><Type>STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>648</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeDefinitionIndexByName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Searches for a recipe definition with the given name and return the found index]]></Comment><ReturnType>INT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>stDefinitionName</Name><Type>STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>648</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>SelectRecipeDefinition</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Selects the recipe definition at the specified index]]></Comment><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>iIndex</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Name><BitSize>32</BitSize><BaseType>UDINT</BaseType></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesActionRecord</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemQuality</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>New</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ The item was not yet monitored. The quality will be assigned when this happened the first time]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Good</Text><Enum>1</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ The item is in good state and it has been monitored at least once]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Bad</Text><Enum>2</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ The item could not be monitored correctly. For details have a look at the according error code.]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IBaseLibrary">TypeClass</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_BOOL</Text><Enum>0</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_BIT</Text><Enum>1</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_BYTE</Text><Enum>2</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_WORD</Text><Enum>3</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_DWORD</Text><Enum>4</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LWORD</Text><Enum>5</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_SINT</Text><Enum>6</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_INT</Text><Enum>7</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_DINT</Text><Enum>8</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LINT</Text><Enum>9</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_USINT</Text><Enum>10</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_UINT</Text><Enum>11</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_UDINT</Text><Enum>12</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ULINT</Text><Enum>13</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_REAL</Text><Enum>14</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LREAL</Text><Enum>15</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_STRING</Text><Enum>16</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_WSTRING</Text><Enum>17</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_TIME</Text><Enum>18</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_DATE</Text><Enum>19</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_DATEANDTIME</Text><Enum>20</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_TIMEOFDAY</Text><Enum>21</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_POINTER</Text><Enum>22</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_REFERENCE</Text><Enum>23</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_SUBRANGE</Text><Enum>24</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ENUM</Text><Enum>25</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ARRAY</Text><Enum>26</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_PARAMS</Text><Enum>27</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_USERDEF</Text><Enum>28</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_NONE</Text><Enum>29</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANY</Text><Enum>30</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANYBIT</Text><Enum>31</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANYDATE</Text><Enum>32</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANYINT</Text><Enum>33</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANYNUM</Text><Enum>34</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANYREAL</Text><Enum>35</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LAZY</Text><Enum>36</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LTIME</Text><Enum>37</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_BITCONST</Text><Enum>38</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_UXINT</Text><Enum>39</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_XWORD</Text><Enum>40</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_XINT</Text><Enum>41</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_XSRTING</Text><Enum>42</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_VARLENARRAY</Text><Enum>43</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_ANYSTRING</Text><Enum>44</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_VECTOR</Text><Enum>45</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LDATE</Text><Enum>46</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LDATEANDTIME</Text><Enum>47</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_LTIMEOFDAY</Text><Enum>48</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>TYPE_INTERFACE</Text><Enum>-4096</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Only for backward compatibility. Is not supported by CoDeSys. In version 3.1.1.1 there
									was this member so we include this value for compatibility. The integer-value is not
									correct! Must not be used ]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>compatibility_id</Name><Value>52A6FD6D-031C-41c0-A818-0F45FE19AF8F</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemBase</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getErrorCode</Name><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getQuality</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemQuality</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getTimeStamp</Name><ReturnType>TIME</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getTypeClass</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IBaseLibrary">TypeClass</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemList</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getCount</Name><ReturnType>UDINT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>Clear</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Clears the list of |IDataItemBase| managed by this list object. Allocated objects will be released.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>CreateAndAdd</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Creates a new item for monitoring and immediately adds it to the list.

 .. note:: Usually items are monitored in total. If you want to expand the items (to prevent problems with different alignment etc.) then consider using the method |IDataItemListExpanding.CreateAndAddExpanding| instead.

 :return: An error code representing the result of the operation. In case of success, ERR_OK will be returned]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pstSymbol</Name><Type PointerTo="1">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetItem</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Returns the item at the given index.
 :return: The item at the index or 0 in case of an invalid index.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemBase</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>udiIndex</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequest</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequestHandling</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>ReleaseRequest</Name><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>request</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequest</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomResponse</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequestCallback</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>RequestFinished</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when the execution of the given request is finished.

 .. note:: The method will be called no matter whether the request was executed successfully or not. Callees can find out about this fact by evaluating the according result.
 ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>request</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequest</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>response</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomResponse</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>result</Name><Type Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICredentials</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICredentialsProvider</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>GetCredentials</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Must return ERR_OK if called after a successfull |ICredentialsProvider.IsGetCredentialsFinished|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>uxiRequestId</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>credentials</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICredentials</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>IsGetCredentialsFinished</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Will return ERR_OK if the request is finished, ERR_PENDING if it is not yet 
 finished, ERR_DS_RETRYLOGIN if the login should be tried again, another error code in case of an error]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>uxiRequestId</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>LoginFailed</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Will be called when a login failed due to wrong credentials
 The behaviour of the datasource afterwards depends on the return value. In case of 
 ERR_PENDING, the logincycle will be started again with a call to GetCredentials.
 In all other cases the driver will go to it's error state.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>uxiRequestId</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>tRetryWaitTime</Name><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>LoginSucceeded</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Will be called when after a successful login.]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>uxiRequestId</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>StartGetCredentials</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Will return an id of the question for credentials. This id can be used in 
 the following calls to |ICredentialsProvider.IsGetCredentialsFinished|]]></Comment><ReturnType>ULINT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pstDataSource</Name><Type PointerTo="1">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>udiErrorCode</Name><Type Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasource</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getCustomRequestHandling</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequestHandling</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>EnqueueCustomRequest</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Enqueues the given request for sending to the connected device the next time this is possible.

 .. note:: It is possible to call this method without holding locks on the datasources (like |IDatasourcesMgr.BeginDataConfiguration|)

 :return: Returns a runtime system error code (see CmpErrors.library) or one of |Errors| representing the result of the operation.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>request</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequest</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>finishedCallback</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICustomRequestCallback</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>SetCredentialsProvider</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Assigns the given credentials provider object to a specific datasource.
 :return: An error code representing the result of the operation]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>provider</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICredentialsProvider</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesMgr</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>ActionRecordDelete</Name><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>record</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesActionRecord</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ActionRecordingGetResult</Name><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>result</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesActionRecord</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ActionRecordingStart</Name><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>ActionRecordReplay</Name><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>record</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesActionRecord</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>AllItemsOk</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will return ERR_OK when all active items of all datasources have the quality good
 else it will return ERR_DS_BADITEMS.
 It might return ERR_DS_MULTITASKING_LOCKED when it is currently not possible to have access to
 all datasources. In this case the client should call this method again later.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>BeginDataConfiguration</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method locks the concurrent task for monitoring items and allows subsequent accesses 
 to the configuration of the active. To unlock again afterwards, call |IDatasourcesMgr.EndDataConfiguration|

 .. important:: Before calling methods like |IDatasourcesMgr.UseData| or |IDatasourcesMgr.ReleaseData| it is necessary to do this syncronisation to prevent undefined behaviour.

 :return: Returns a runtime system error code (see CmpErrors.library) or one of |Errors|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>xBlocking</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>CreateItemList</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Creates a new item list that can be used for reading/writing synchronously for example.

 .. important:: Please remark that you have to release the returned object when it is no longer in use by calling |IDatasourcesMgr.DeleteItemList|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemList</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>udiInitialCapacity</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>DeleteItemList</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Deletes an item list and the items managed therin that was previously created using |IDatasourcesMgr.CreateItemList|
 :return: An error code representing the result of the operation. In case of success, ERR_OK will be returned]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>itemsList</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemList</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>EndDataConfiguration</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Releases a previously taken lock by |IDatasourcesMgr.BeginDataConfiguration| 
 :return: Returns a runtime system error code (see CmpErrors.library) or one of |Errors|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize></Method><Method><Name>GetDatasource</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Returns the datasource representing the given object's name. 
 :return: The datasource object or 0 in case there is none with the given name.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasource</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>name</Name><Type>STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>648</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetItemInfo</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemBase</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pstSymbol</Name><Type PointerTo="1">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ReadItemsSync</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Reads the given list of items synchronously. 

 .. important:: Please remark that the operation might take quite some time in case many items are contained within the list. For this time, the call is blocking!]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>items</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemList</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ReleaseData</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Deactivates the item of the given instance path from monitoring.

 .. note:: The items are reference counted so each call to |IDatasourcesMgr.UseData| or |IDatasourcesMgr3.UseDataExpanding| requires a matching call to ReleaseData

 :return: Returns a runtime system error code (see CmpErrors.library) or one of |Errors|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pstSymbol</Name><Type PointerTo="1">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>SetCredentialsProvider</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Assigns the given credentials provider object to all datasources.
 :return: An error code representing the result of the operation]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>provider</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ICredentialsProvider</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>UseData</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Activates the item of the given instance path for monitoring.

 .. note:: The items are reference counted so each call to |IDatasourcesMgr.UseData| requires a matching call to |IDatasourcesMgr.ReleaseData|

 .. note:: Usually items are monitored in total. If you want to expand the items (to prevent problems with different alignment etc.) then consider using the method |IDatasourcesMgr3.UseDataExpanding| instead.

 :return: Returns a runtime system error code (see CmpErrors.library) or one of |Errors|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>pstSymbol</Name><Type PointerTo="1">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>WriteItemsSync</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Writes the given list of items synchronously. 

 .. important:: Please remark that the operation might take quite some time in case many items are contained within the list. For this time, the call is blocking!]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>items</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemList</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemNameType</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>NormalString</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ The name represents a POINTER TO a zero terminated STRING of the according length. Take care when derefercing using IEC operators! ]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Name><BitSize>128</BitSize><SubItem><Name>nameType</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemNameType</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>nameData</Name><Type PointerTo="1">BYTE</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">INotificationClient</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType>IQueryInterface</ExtendsType><Method><Name>ListOperationDone</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when an operation on a list of variables was executed (eg. |IDatasourcesMgr.ReadItemsSync| or |IDatasourcesMgr.WriteItemsSync|) ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>xWriting</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>datasourceName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>result</Name><Type Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ListOperationStart</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when an operation on a list of variables will be executed (eg. |IDatasourcesMgr.ReadItemsSync| or |IDatasourcesMgr.WriteItemsSync|) ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>xWriting</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>datasourceName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ListValueRead</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a variable was read as part of a list operation (see |INotificationClient.ListOperationStart| or |INotificationClient.ListOperationDone|)]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>remoteName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pReadValue</Name><Type PointerTo="1">BYTE</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueType</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IBaseLibrary">TypeClass</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueSize</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ListValueWrite</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a variable will be written as part of a list operation (see |INotificationClient.ListOperationStart| or |INotificationClient.ListOperationDone|)

 .. note:: 
		Please remark that this method will be called before the write operation is sent to the connected device. 
		For being sure about a successful execution the followup call of |INotificationClient.ListOperationDone| should be checked.  ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>remoteName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pWriteValue</Name><Type PointerTo="1">BYTE</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueType</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IBaseLibrary">TypeClass</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueSize</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ReadRequestDone</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a read operation on one or more variables was executed. ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>datasourceName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>result</Name><Type Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>ReadRequestStart</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a read operation on one or more variables will be executed. ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>datasourceName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>SingleValueRead</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a variable was read from the connected device]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>remoteName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pReadValue</Name><Type PointerTo="1">BYTE</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueType</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IBaseLibrary">TypeClass</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueSize</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>SingleValueWrite</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a variable will be written to the connected device

 .. note:: 
		Please remark that this method will be called before the write operation is sent to the connected device. 
		For being sure about a successful execution the followup call of |INotificationClient.WriteRequestDone| should be checked.  ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>remoteName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pOldValue</Name><Type PointerTo="1">BYTE</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pNewValue</Name><Type PointerTo="1">BYTE</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueType</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IBaseLibrary">TypeClass</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>valueSize</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>WriteRequestDone</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a write operation on one or more variables was executed. ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>datasourceName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>result</Name><Type Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>WriteRequestStart</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method will be called when a write operation on one or more variables will be executed. ]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>datasourceName</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">ItemName</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">PersistantItemListUsage</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>Unspecified</Text><Enum>0</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>Recipes</Text><Enum>1</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ The variable list is used for reading or writing recipes. Therefore it is expected that
 the usage details reflect the name of the recipe definition and that all variables of the recipe definition are added
 to the according list.]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemListPersistant</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemList</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getUsage</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">PersistantItemListUsage</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getUsageDetails</Name><ReturnType>WSTRING(80)</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>1296</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>FinishedAdding</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method must be called by users of such a list once the insertion of items (using |IDAtaItemList.CreateAndAdd|)
 is finished. Afterwards the list can be registered within the affected datasource(s). After calling this method it
 is no longer possible to add additional items.
 :return: An error code representing the result of this operation.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize></Method><Properties><Property><Name>TcPlcInterfaceType</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesMgr2</Name><BitSize>64</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDatasourcesMgr</ExtendsType><Method><Name>__getPersistantItemListCount</Name><ReturnType>INT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>16</ReturnBitSize><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>AddNotificationClient</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ This method can be used to register an implementation of |INotificationClient| that will be notified about
 operations of the datasources.
 
 .. note:: Please remark that the number of notification clients might be limited so at least if registering several clients the return value should be evaluated.

 .. note:: The registered object can be removed using |IDatasourcesMgr2.RemoveNotificationClient| 

 :return: An error code that signals whether the registration was successful.]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>client</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">INotificationClient</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>CreatePersistantItemList</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Creates an item list that will be registered automatically within the affected datasources
 after (re)connections of these datasources. An according list can be used in followup calls to
 |IDatasourcesMgr.ReadItemsSync| or |IDatasourcesMgr.WriteItemsSync|

 .. important:: Having such lists might slow down the connection 
 			   setup because the list has to be registered within the connected device!
  
 .. important:: Using this method and the related ones working on the list requires according locking around using |IDatasourcesMgr2.Lock| and |IDatasourcesMgr2.Unlock|
 
 .. note:: It is not supported to register several lists for the same usecase. 
 
 .. note:: Once the list is no longer necessary, it can be deleted using
			  |IDatasourcesMgr2.DeletePersistantItemList|]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemListPersistant</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>usage</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">PersistantItemListUsage</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>usageDetails</Name><Type>WSTRING(80)</Type><BitSize>1296</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>udiInitialCapacity</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>result</Name><Type Namespace="BPLog.CAA.SysCpuHandling.SysTypes">RTS_IEC_RESULT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>DeletePersistantItemList</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Deletes a formerly created |IDataItemListPersistant|
  
 .. important:: Using this method and the related ones working on the list requires according locking around using |IDatasourcesMgr2.Lock| and |IDatasourcesMgr2.Unlock|
]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>itemsList</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management.IDatasources">IDataItemListPersistant</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>GetPersistantItemList</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Returns the nth |IDataItemListPersistant| managed by the current instance. Can be used
