 It overrides the storage path which is normally configured in the recipe manager configuration.

 :return: TRUE, if the storage path was set successfully. 

 Possible error reasons are:
		- |ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET|
		- The recipe management contains no recipe definition

 See :ref:`ReturnValues` for a description of all possible errors.]]></Comment><ReturnType>BOOL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>8</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>stPath</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ The storage path i.e. c:/recipes/ ]]></Comment><Type>STRING(512)</Type><BitSize>4104</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>dwResult</Name><Type>DWORD</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>recipeDefinition</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>pPersistentRecipeHelper</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management" PointerTo="1">IPersistentRecipeHelper</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>ReadAndSaveRecipeAs</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Reads the current PLC values into the recipe and afterwards stores the recipe into the specified recipe file

 The content of an existing file will be overridden.

 Attention: The behaviour from this method has changed in the following way. If both parameters "RecipeDefinitionName" and "RecipeName" are set (``stringlength`` > 0) the behaviour is not changed. In this case a read to a specific recipe does also an 
 automatically save to the recipe when the option "Save recipes changes to recipe files automatically" is set in the RecipeManager configuration "General".
 If the ``RecipeName`` is not set (``stringlength`` = 0) the behaviour has changed. In this case an automatically save to the recipe is not executed and the new recipe values are only stored into the given file name.
 :return: Possible last error values:

		- |ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_SAVE_ERR|
		- |ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET|
		- |ERR_OK|

 See :ref:`ReturnValues` for a description of all possible errors.]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>RecipeDefinitionName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe definition. ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>RecipeName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe. ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>FileName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the file ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(255)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Local><Name>_RecipeDefinition</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>pPersistentRecipeHelper</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management" PointerTo="1">IPersistentRecipeHelper</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>recSel</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeSelection</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>prvSetRecipeDefinition</Name><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>RecipeDefinitionName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Name of the recipe definition ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>RecipeName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Local><Name>nRecipeIndex</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Loca