		- |ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET|
		- |ERR_OK|

 See :ref:`ReturnValues` for a description of all possible errors.]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>RecipeDefinitionName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe definition. ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>prvGetRecipeDefintionByName</Name><ReturnType Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>stRecipeDef</Name><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Properties><Property><Name>conditionalshow</Name><Value>visu_coredev</Value></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>prvCreateRecipeHelp</Name><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>RecipeDefinitionName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Name of the recipe definition ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>RecipeName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>bSave</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>def</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>conditionalshow</Name><Value>visu_coredev</Value></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>GetRecipeValuesSizeOf</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Returns the recipe values from the corresponding recipe.

 **Example:**

 We have 50 recipe values. We want to create a table which shows 10 recipe values at the same time.
 We define a string array ``strArr: ARRAY[0..9] OF STRING;``
 Corresponding to the ``iStartIndex`` we can get the recipe values from a specific area.

 	- ``iStartIndex`` := 0; The values 0..9 are returned.
 	- ``iStartIndex`` := 20; The values 20..29 are returned.

 In this example:

 	- ``iSizeOfString`` := TO_INT(SIZE_OF(strArr[0])); 
 	- ``iSize`` := 10;
 :return: Possible last error values:

		- |ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET|
		- |ERR_OK|

 See :ref:`ReturnValues` for a description of all possible errors.]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>RecipeDefinitionName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe definition. ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>RecipeName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe. ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>pStrings</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ The strings where the recipe values should be stored. ]]></Comment><Type>STRING(80)</Type><ArrayInfo PointerTo="1"><LBound>0</LBound><Elements>1</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>64</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iSize</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Size of the string array. ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iStartIndex</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Start index. Can be used for a scrolling function. (See example).]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>iSizeOfString</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Size of a string in the pStrings array. It should correspond to the actual number of bytes provided by the SIZEOF operator. ]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>recipeDefinition3</Name><Type Namespace="Recipe_Management">IRecipeDefinition3</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>CreateRecipe</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Creates a new recipe in the given recipe definition

 The method reads the current PLC values to the new recipe and saves them as a recipe file with the default name. 
 The default name is ``<recipe>.<recipe definition>.<recipe extension>``. At the end the new recipe would be stored in the default file.

 :return: Possible last error values:

		- |ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_ALREADY_EXIST|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_NOMEMORY|
		- |ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET|
		- |ERR_OK|

 See :ref:`ReturnValues` for a description of all possible errors.]]></Comment><ReturnType>DWORD</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>RecipeDefinitionName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[	Name of the recipe definition ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>RecipeName</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Name of the recipe ]]></Comment><Type ReferenceTo="true">STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>InOut</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>DeleteRecipeFile</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Removes the standard recipe file from a recipe

 The standard recipe file has the file name ``<recipe>.<recipedefinition>.<extension>``.

 :return: Possible last error values:

		- |ERR_RECIPE_DEFINITION_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_RECIPE_FILE_NOT_FOUND|
		- |ERR_NO_RECIPE_MANAGER_SET|
